00:59:02,460 --> 00:59:12,300
1.01. To translate that into English, the women who were on estrogen only had a 21% risk reduction,

592
00:59:12,300 --> 00:59:17,820
but the 95% confidence interval crossed unity, which meant it was not statistically significant.

593
00:59:17,820 --> 00:59:23,340
The P value was 0.07 if my memory serves me correctly, which meant there was a 7% chance

594
00:59:23,340 --> 00:59:28,300
that that effect was random, meaning it didn't hit the 5% threshold. Right. But I remember that

595
00:59:28,300 --> 00:59:36,620
mostly. Pretty, pretty close. The fact is there was no real increase among the women who got

